# Open Design MCP — UI source of truth

For **any** UI/UX work in this repo (new screens, layout, styling, components, handbook/copilot presentation, copy-button UX, etc.), **start with Open Design MCP** (`user-open-design`). Do not guess UI from memory or screenshots alone.

## Required workflow

1. **Check OD** — Call `get_active_context` or `list_projects`. If no active project, use `project: "pluto2-main"` or the name the user gives (e.g. Result Page, handbook).
2. **Pull design first** — Prefer `get_artifact()` for the full bundle (entry + tokens CSS + related files). Use `get_file` / `search_files` only when you need one known path.
3. **Read tool schemas** — Inspect MCP tool descriptors under `mcps/user-open-design/tools/` before calling `CallMcpTool`.
4. **Implement in repo** — Match OD typography, spacing, colors, and patterns in `templates/`, `static/css/`, `static/js/`.
5. **New UI in OD** — For net-new layouts, use `create_artifact` in Open Design when appropriate, then implement from the generated files.

## Scope

| Use Open Design MCP | Skip OD (code-only) |
|---------------------|---------------------|
| HTML templates, CSS, front-end JS presentation | Python routes, DB, APIs, LLM prompts |
| Handbook result workspace, copilot, dashboards | Tests, security, backend refactors |

## If Open Design is unavailable

Tell the user OD must be running locally. Offer to proceed with existing repo patterns only after they confirm, and re-sync with OD when it is back.

## Default projects

- App shell / Co-Pilot: `pluto2-main` (entry `index2.html`)
- Handbook / result experiments: user-named OD projects (e.g. `Result Page -`, `handbook`)

Active OD context expires ~5 minutes after last interaction; pass `project` explicitly when needed.
